comment: He tried his best to make the readings interesting by adding funny voices when reading the material. His work is straight forward and asks for minimal work back from student. The most important part is trying to listen to the readings which can be hard because the content of the stuff can be pretty confusing.

I dunno wtf these ppl are talking about this prof is sooo easy. I wouldn't pay attention to half the stuff we read in literature in english I and I still got a B+. All you gotta do is ask him what specific readings are going to be on the final test and have a brief understanding of them. He was super nice and fair

Even though I was advanced, he showed me new ways of working with the subject texts and he gave me feedback that made me a better critic--he is also very understanding one on one--he is fun to spend time with in social situations--so smart and nice
very dedicated to teaching and always willing to help

He was a great professor. I loved his lectures because he always knew what he was talking about. Hardly reads from notes, is very intelligent. Knows all the material to such a great extent. Great middle english accent. Great insight to all texts. If you want a professor who knows what he is talking about, he is the way to go.

I actually enjoyed his class, maybe b/c English is my favorite subject.His essays can be a bit too much, yet it helps you in the long run. One thing I love about his class are the random stories, which actually fits with the subject of discussion. But beware,you must buy the books for his class.
has to be one of the best english professors i've had in my college career thus far; provides insightful commentary on the texts; you learn A LOT if you pay close attention
very bright, does a great middle english accent, quite funny at times, hes a good prof
He is my favorite teacher so far.  The reading is pretty difficult, but I've learned alot about writing.  Very helpful one on one.
really interesting lectures, ties in ideas from one play to the next.  Hard grader, but fair and helpful.  Best english class I've taken.
He is a wonderful teacher. Very intelligent. Hard to catch him during office hours, but other than that very fair.
Amazing man, cool professor, kind generous. taking an english class you cant go wrong with him at all, trust me.
He knew what he was talking about, but it came across dry.  He judged me unfairly, and by the end of the semster he still didn't know my name.
has a lot of knowledge and is easy to get along with in general, class boring
Dr. Lederer is an amazing professor. Every time I leave her class I feel inspired in the field of Speech-Language Pathology

she talks to us like babies and the class she teaches, 400, is complete BS and since we have no choice but to take that class be prepared to hate it like we do. we don't even talk about current issues, rather we take pointless "field trips" and she's making us teach other the last couple weeks of class with the BS project that has to be 2 hrs long
One of the most fake people I have ever met. Boring and likes to act like she's teaching a kindergarten class with her annoying assignments. She should retire early
Not very hard, but not a great teacher. Strays off topic. Tests are ok.
No Comments
She is an asset to the field, but her class is too divurgent, a lot of discussion, but not enough preparation for the clinic.
